Model notes / glossary
Quick definitions of terms used in this report and what the model uses as input.
What this is
Daily win probabilities + model-implied moneylines, with team-profile radars and a frozen-accuracy backtest.
Model inputs & training
The model starts by learning what a strong NHL team looks like using MoneyPuck’s 2024–25 team data. It looks at team performance measures like expected goals, shot quality and volume, special teams, goal differential, and goaltending — the same metrics shown on the radar charts. Those 2024 patterns are used to create a baseline team-strength score, which is then applied to the current season. For each matchup, the model compares the two teams to get an initial win probability. That baseline is then adjusted for real-world context: how each team has played recently, how much rest each team has had, whether a team performs better at home or on the road, short-term shot and xG trends from the MoneyPuck shots dataset, and any manual injury adjustments if configured. ESPN odds are shown only as a reference point (including devigged ‘fair’ probabilities) and do not influence the model’s prediction unless explicitly added.
Win probability
Model-estimated chance of the predicted winner winning the game.
Model ML
Moneyline derived from the model probability (no vigorish).
ESPN ML
Market moneyline pulled from ESPN (may include vig).
Devig
If both sides are available, market implied probs are normalized so home+away=1 (a ‘fair’ reference).
Confidence buckets
Very High ≥ 72% · High ≥ 65% · Medium ≥ 58% · Low ≥ 50% · otherwise N/A.
Frozen predictions
Predictions are snapshotted into prediction_history.csv when games become upcoming; accuracy uses only those frozen rows.
Radars
Each spoke is a team percentile vs league for that metric (higher = stronger). Filled areas use secondary team color.
Radar metrics (FEATURES)
• xGoals% (share of expected goals) (xGoalsPercentage)
• Fenwick% (unblocked shot attempt share) (fenwickPercentage)
• xGoals For / 60 (xGoalsForPer60)
• xGoals Diff / 60 (for − against) (xGoalsDiffPer60)
• Shots Diff / 60 (SOG for − against) (shotsDiffPer60)
• High-Danger Diff / 60 (highDangerDiffPer60)
• Shot Credit Diff (score-adjusted) (shotCreditDiff)
• Penalty Diff (for − against) (penaltyDiff)
• Goal Diff (for − against) (goalDiff)
• Save% (approx; saved SOG / SOG against) (savePct)
xG shot-form
Optional adjustment from MoneyPuck shots: rolling window=10 games, scaled by 0.35, capped at 0.75.
Recency form
Margin-weighted recent form over last 10 games; blended with weight 0.3.
Rest / fatigue
Rest differential term with weight 0.1 and clip ±3 days.
Home/road split
Home-vs-road performance delta with weight 0.2 and prior=20 games.
What to watch
Higher confidence ≠ guarantee; look for injuries/goalies/news that the model doesn’t fully capture.
Model-driven probabilities — not betting advice.
Accuracy/quality uses frozen predictions from prediction_history.csv and completed games only.
